track.name: St. James Infirmary
comments: You could learn to play the trumpet just for this song alone. It's woth that.
This is so haunting, but it brings a smile to my face. Amazing.
this song is so beautiful and so sad at the same time.

That's the thing about streaming on lastfm though. There are multiple versions under the same name. Some people will get the wrong one and some of us will be lucky enough to actually hear Satchmo doing it right.
Not sure this version is Armstrong. I know it's not him singing. Still a nice version.
"but she'll never find a sweet man like me..." hehehhehe
OMG! I love this so, so much. Mother of mercy, how I love it!
Love this song. Loved playing it in Dixie Band too. Great tune.
Had to stop cooking to listen properly, made my afternoon.
It's a beautiful shade of melancholy.
Even on a song like this,he puts a smile on my face.
